<h2>Enrol a product for accessibility management</h2>

<p>Enrolling a product in the accessibility management system allows you to track accessibility issues, manage statements, and ensure compliance with accessibility standards.</p>

<h3>Access requirements</h3>
<p>Only users with <strong>Super Admin</strong> or <strong>Admin</strong> roles can enrol products for accessibility management.</p>

<h3>How to enrol a product</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Apps → Accessibility Issues and Statements</strong></li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Enrol Product</strong> button in the top right</li>
    <li>Select the product you want to enrol from the dropdown</li>
    <li>Configure the following settings:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>SLA Response Days:</strong> Number of days to respond to accessibility complaints</li>
            <li><strong>Complaint Contact Email:</strong> Email address for accessibility complaints</li>
            <li><strong>WCAG Target Version:</strong> Target WCAG version (e.g., 2.1)</li>
            <li><strong>WCAG Target Level:</strong> Target compliance level (A, AA, or AAA)</li>
            <li><strong>Statement URL:</strong> Optional existing statement URL</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Enrol Product</strong> to complete the enrolment</li>
</ol>

<h3>What happens after enrolment</h3>
<ul>
    <li>The product appears in the accessibility management dashboard</li>
    <li>You can start tracking accessibility issues for the product</li>
    <li>A hosted accessibility statement can be generated</li>
    <li>Product contacts from the CMS are automatically linked</li>
    <li>The product is included in accessibility reporting and dashboards</li>
</ul>

<h3>Managing enrolled products</h3>
<p>Once enrolled, you can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>View product details in the accessibility dashboard</li>
    <li>Track and manage accessibility issues</li>
    <li>Generate and verify accessibility statements</li>
    <li>Record accessibility audits</li>
    <li>Update product settings and contacts</li>
</ul>

<h3>Statement verification</h3>
<p>After enrolment, you can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Generate a hosted accessibility statement</li>
    <li>Provide the live product URL for automatic verification</li>
    <li>Manually verify statement installation if automatic checks can't access the site</li>
    <li>Monitor verification status in the dashboard</li>
</ul>

